	"description": "As developers, we all use some form of version control system, and the most\npopular one is Git. \n\nA lot of us use Git, but very few know how it really works under the hood. We\nmostly just use it with a GUI client or the ones built into our IDEs and code\neditors. Some of us (myself included) don&#x27;t even know how to navigate it using\nthe terminal. \n\nThis can be detrimental to your projects, as you might run into issues which you\nwon&#x27;t know how to resolve without fully understanding how Git works on",
